### Example API Requests
### Use with REST Client extension in VS Code
### Click "Send Request" above any request to execute it

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api

### 1. Create a Post - Basketball Game
POST {{baseUrl}}/posts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Basketball Game at Central Park",
  "activityType": "sports",
  "latitude": 40.7829,
  "longitude": -73.9654,
  "scheduledTime": "2026-02-15T18:00:00Z",
  "createdById": "user-123"
}

###

### 2. Create a Post - Coffee Meetup
POST {{baseUrl}}/posts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Coffee & Code Session",
  "activityType": "coffee",
  "latitude": 40.7580,
  "longitude": -73.9855,
  "scheduledTime": "2026-02-01T10:00:00Z",
  "createdById": "user-456"
}

###

### 3. Create a Post - Dinner Party
POST {{baseUrl}}/posts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Basketball Pickup Game",
  "activityType": "basketball",
  "latitude": 40.7150,
  "longitude": -74.0070,
  "scheduledTime": "2026-02-01T15:00:00Z",
  "createdById": "user-789"
}

###

### 4. Get Nearby Posts (from user location)
GET {{baseUrl}}/posts/nearby?latitude=40.7128&longitude=-74.0060

###

### 5. Get Nearby Posts (different location)
GET {{baseUrl}}/posts/nearby?latitude=40.7580&longitude=-73.9855

###

### 6. Get Post by ID (replace with actual ID from create response)
GET {{baseUrl}}/posts/{{postId}}

###

### 7. Join a Post (replace with actual IDs)
POST {{baseUrl}}/posts/{{postId}}/join
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "user-999"
}

###

### 8. Get User's Posts
GET {{baseUrl}}/posts/user/user-123

###

### Test Coordinates
# New York City: 40.7128, -74.0060
# Times Square: 40.7580, -73.9855
# Central Park: 40.7829, -73.9654
# Brooklyn: 40.6782, -73.9442
# Queens: 40.7282, -73.7949
